The paper discusses the use of deep neural networks (DNNs) in various artificial intelligence tasks, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The focus of the paper is on improving the precision of DNN models, which is a common problem in machine learning and falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper specifically mentions object recognition and natural language processing, which are both subfields of computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.NE), respectively. Finally, the paper proposes a tool for analyzing the data flow of DNN models, which is related to software engineering (cs.SE).
